tudies, and dramatic composition, and goes on to consider in detail various productions of the works of Wagner, Mozart, Verdi, and Alexander Zemlinsky. Ultimately, the book seeks to initiate a dialogue between scholars of music, literature, and performance by addressing questions raised in each field in a manner that influences them all.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  azemlinsky, wagner, verdi, mozart, opera, adaptation, staging, performance, performing arts, music, theater, production, literature, dramaturgy, directing, textuality, interpretation, dramatic composition, mise en scene, reading, die meistersinger von nurnberg, fidelity, translation, imagination, creativity, le nozze di figaro, entfushrung aus dem serail, sublimation, audacity, don carlos, der konig kandaules.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022647522640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226475257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226475257/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles